1. THE PHYSICS OF VFT CRYPTOBIOSIS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
In biology and materials science, "VFT" stands for the Vogel-Fulcher-Tammann equation. 
It describes the temperature dependence of viscosity in glass-forming liquids. When an organism (like a tardigrade) enters "Cryptobiosis" to survive extreme freezing, its cellular water doesn't crystallize into ice (which would shatter the cell walls). Instead, it undergoes "Vitrification" — hardening into an amorphous biological glass, preserving the macro-structure perfectly at near-zero metabolic states.

